    Class Description
    AccessPeriod
    This class is used for the access period to the registration system.
    Course
    The course class is an entity that holds information regarding a course.
    createCourseData
    Class used to pre-load course data into the database.
    createSchoolData
    Class used to pre-load school data into the database.
    createStaffData
    Class used to pre-load staff data into the database.
    createStudentData
    Class used to pre-load student data into the database.
    createUserData  
    customSystem
    The custom system class provides a UI to the user that can be used to access the student or staff accounts.
    DatabaseControl
    The DatabaseControl class defines methods that facilitate easy access to the user and school records in terms of courses, classes, enrollments, and so on..
    Email
    Class email is a specific implementation of the notification interface, which has been adapted to send emails notifications to the students.
    GetData  
    Hash
    Hash is used to encode the user password, such that it is stored in a format only understood by the machine.
    Index
    Index contains the information about a particular index in the course.
    Lab
    Class Lab extends from Lesson, and is a specific type of lesson.
    Lecture
    Class Lecture extends from lesson, and is a specific type of lesson.
    Lesson
    Lesson is an abstract class that can be used to extend to different types of classes in terms of this application.
    Notification
    A notification interface that contains methods to send different types of messages depending on the use case.
    Password
    Password provides a class for the storage of students or staff passwords in their hashed format.
    PasswordField
    PasswordField is an entity that is used when entering sensitive information on the console.
    School
    School class unique attributes for a particular school.
    SerializeDB
    The SerializeDB class provides the the static methods that handles the serialization and deserialization of Objects in the background.
    Staff
    Staff is a specific implementation of a user.
    StaffControl  
    StaffUI
    Provides an interface UI and the corresponding methods for a staff member to access and modify the database with staff level access.
    Student
    Student is a specific implementation of a user.
    StudentControl
    StudentControl is used to provide student level access of the database and student privileges after successful login to the database.
    StudentUI
    Provides an interface UI and the corresponding methods for a student to access and modify the database with student level access.
    StudentUIMsg
    Boundary class responsible for displaying items that are specific to the student.
    Tutorial
    Class Tutorial extends from lesson, and is a specific type of lesson.
    User
    User is a top-level class that defines a user on a general level.
    WorkingHours
    The WorkingHours class stores a time range, and has custom functions to check the validity of the timings passed to it, as well as to convert them into a usable format.
